wiki.content: “Virgo’s Groove” is one of the most sex-influenced tracks on the album. Beyoncé’s zodiac sign is a Virgo since she was born on September 4. As one of the three earth signs, who are considered the most grounded out of them all, Virgos' sex life rely heavily on physical touch and closeness to someone. They are known to be really lusty, sensual, have high libido and are considered best in bed when they’re with someone they love, trust and have some sort of connection with. Even though Virgos are considered patient lovers, Bey’s expressing the tension she feels as she can’t wait no more. She and her lover don’t have time like they used to, so she’s calling him to come, as her excitement is getting bigger and taking over her. This is the second time Beyoncé is mentioning Virgo in her music, previously done on her debut album Dangerously in Love with track 14 called “Gift from Virgo.” Read more on Last.fm.
